1.   mailx -f ~/mbox
2.   set VISUAL=/usr/bin/vim   
3.   set EDITOR=/usr/bin/vim
4.   :n
5.   .
6.   d (from doug.jones)
7.   mailx -a ~/.mailrc -s"Delete this message" doug.jones < /dev/null
8.   ~v
9.   h
10.  z-
11.  Mv 
12.  x
13.  set VISULAL=/usr/bin/vim, set EDITOR/usr/bin/vim. I choose these commands because of the value they add to reading and writing mail messages. Aside from this, I have not found other commands to add.
